@startuml PY-006-datamodel
title PY-006 · XP Values per Path Level — Data Model

skinparam backgroundColor #1e1e2e
skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor #2a2a3d
  BorderColor #555577
  FontColor #cdd6f4
  HeaderBackgroundColor #313244
}
skinparam ArrowColor #89b4fa
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #313244
skinparam NoteBorderColor #555577
skinparam NoteFontColor #cdd6f4

entity "Path (in skills.json)" as Path {
  * level     : "easy" | "mid" | "hard"
  * xpReward  : number
  --
  easy  → 50 XP
  mid   → 100 XP
  hard  → 150 XP
}

note right of Path
  XP values are defined per-path
  in content/skills.json.
  No code changes needed to
  adjust XP — edit the JSON.
end note

entity "PathCompletion (localStorage)" as Completion {
  * key   : "dragonpy-progress"
  --
  Stored as:
  {
    "<skillId>": ["easy", "mid", "hard"]
  }

  xpEarned is derived at runtime:
    sum of xpReward for each
    completed level
}

entity "ExerciseData (markdown frontmatter)" as Exercise {
  * skillId        : string
  * level          : "easy" | "mid" | "hard"
  * starterCode    : string   ← scaffolding decreases per level
  * expectedOutput : string
  * xpReward       : number   ← must match skills.json
  --
  easy  → guided, most code provided
  mid   → partial scaffold, learner fills more
  hard  → minimal guidance, learner solves alone
}

note bottom of Exercise
  Scaffolding level is expressed
  in starterCode content, not code.
  Easy: structure + gaps.
  Mid:  skeleton only.
  Hard: blank or one-liner prompt.
end note

Path "1" -- "1" Exercise : describes
Path "1" --o{ "0..1" Completion : recorded when complete

@enduml
